Gauteng hopes to have 15,000 more beds for Covid-19 patients by the middle of August. Health MEC, Bandile Masuku, says the province currently has 9000 beds. The province has seen a surge in cases recently and is expecting a peak between August and September. eNCA’s Lindokuhle Xulu was with the MEC in Soshanguve in Tshwane and filed this report. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Gauteng hopes to have 15,000 more beds for COVID-19 patients by the middle of August. Health MEC, Bandile Masuku, says the province currently has 9,000 beds. The province has seen a surge in cases recently and is expecting a peak between August and September. WATCH: Gauteng sees surge in active COVID-19 cases “We are bracing ourselves for a peak. We are not yet there,” said Masuku. “The numbers are just showing us that this is an expected peak, the expected increase we were actually planning in terms of modelling,” said Masuku. Masuku said field hospitals are being set up to increase the number of available beds. The provincial government is confident the province will be ready. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.